---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Calculator from '../components/Calculator.jsx';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Tesla Model 3 Charging Cost | Voltloop"
  description="How much does it cost to charge a Tesla Model 3 at home or at a Supercharger? Get an instant estimate."
>
  <h1>How much does it cost to charge a Tesla Model 3?</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    A Tesla Model 3 Long Range has a ~75 kWh battery. Charging from 20% to 80% at the
    U.S. average home rate of $0.16/kWh costs about <strong>$7.20</strong>. The same
    top-up at a Supercharger ($0.36/kWh) is closer to <strong>$16</strong>.
  </p>

  <Calculator
    client:load
    batterySize={75}
    currentPercent={20}
    targetPercent={80}
    ratePerKwh={0.16}
    chargerType="L2"
  />

  <h2>Home vs Supercharger</h2>
  <table class="compare">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Where you charge</th>
        <th>Typical $/kWh</th>
        <th>20→80% on Model 3 (~45 kWh)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Home Level 2</td><td>$0.16</td><td>$7.20</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Public Level 2</td><td>$0.25</td><td>$11.25</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Tesla Supercharger</td><td>$0.36</td><td>$16.20</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Per-mile cost</h2>
  <p>
    The Model 3 averages roughly <strong>4 mi/kWh</strong>. At $0.16/kWh that's about
    <strong>$0.04/mile</strong> — well under half the cost of a 30 mpg gas car at $4/gallon.
  </p>

  <p>
    See also the <a href="/tesla-supercharger-cost">Tesla Supercharger cost</a> page or the
    <a href="/ev-charging-cost-calculator">general EV charging calculator</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
